sentences: Belinda Metz (born January 4, 1960) is a Canadian solo recording artist from the early to mid-1980s who has since gone into acting.
In 1982 Metz released an independent album, The Minx, on Quantum Records.

Signed to a recording contract in 1985 with Attic Records, she released a full-length album, Electric Splash, which contained her only hit single, "What About Me", and won her a "Most Promising Female Vocalist" award from the U-Knows, CFNY's listener's choice awards.
In 1985 Metz was severely injured in a car accident.
Recently, she had a role as Irene the band manager in the  Disney Channel Original Series So Weird.
She continues to act in television and movies, most recently Eight Below as well as doing voice over work for corporations like Telus.
